  "title": "Audit Associate",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Title: Audit Associate</strong></p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p>• Execute audit procedures in detailed financial analysis, testing internal controls, and assessing compliance with accounting standards.</p><p>• Identify significant accounting and auditing issues via engagements in the various industries.</p><p>• Obtain audit evidence and document observations in the audit work paper.</p><p>• Must be able to work with different engagement managers and team members.</p><p>• Awareness of self-development and self-enhancement of professional skill sets for career.</p><p>• Communicate effectively.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><p>· Bachelor's or master’s degree in Accountancy, Finance or Professional Qualification in Accountancy, such as ACCA, CA, ICAEW and CPA Australia.</p><p>· General knowledge of economic trends, technical and industry developments, and a sense of business operations.</p><p>· Minimum 2 years of auditing or accounting experience preferred.</p><p>· Fresh graduates are welcome to apply for the Audit Associate role.</p><p>· Good time management and good documentation skills.</p><p>· Strong English communication skills, both verbal and written.</p><p>· Display accountability and a spirit of teamwork.</p><p>· Demonstrate initiative</p>",
